<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1435,1107,1160]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,298,1107,1129]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">FIGURE 2-1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bordoni" authorityYear="2013" box="[307,575,1107,1129]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megalinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hailuogouensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[307,575,1107,1129]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Megalinus hailuogouensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[584,667,1108,1129]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[584,667,1108,1129]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
: A. male tergite VIII; B. male sternite VIII; C. male sternite IX; D. male tergite X; E. median lobe of aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bars 0.30 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1204,1949]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,385,1204,1229]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="1">Mesoscutellum.</emphasis>
Shiny, extensively covered with polygonal reticulum, and with paired punctures on anterior 1/3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1204,1949]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis box="[199,393,1276,1301]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,275,1276,1301]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Elytra</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[290,380,1276,1301]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="11.[151,249,1799,1821]" captionTargetBox="[178,1407,419,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-122@11.[151,1436,409,1778]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 2. Forebody: A. Megalinus hailuogouensis sp. nov.; B. M. ningxiaensis sp. nov.; C. M. tangi sp. nov. Scale bars 0.30 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Subquadrated (EL to EW ratio 1.1), obviously wider than pronotum, but longer. Humeri well developed, lateral margins widened posteriorly, hind margin subtruncated. Integument shiny and flattened, without microsculpture; each elytron with 8–9 rows of medium-sized punctures; deflexed portion with 7–8 rows of punctures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1204,1949]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1420,1445]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="1">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Cylindrical, broadest at segment VI. Tergites III–VII shiny, covered with superficial transverse microstriae and small setiferous punctures, interspaces between punctures near 2–3 punctures’ diameter, denser laterobasally; each tergite with basal impression, which impunctate, but bearing distinct polygonal reticulum. Surface between two basal transverse carinae impunctate, but bearing distinct transverse microstriae. All abdominal sternites shiny, with microsculpture and setiferous punctures as those on tergites.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1204,1949]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1600,1625]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Male</emphasis>
. Abdominal segment VIII entirely covered with setiferous punctures, except a narrow medial longitudinal impunctate band; posterior margins of tergite VIII slightly emarginated or subtruncated (
<figureCitation box="[1308,1378,1636,1661]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="11.[151,249,1799,1821]" captionTargetBox="[178,1407,419,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-122@11.[151,1436,409,1778]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 2. Forebody: A. Megalinus hailuogouensis sp. nov.; B. M. ningxiaensis sp. nov.; C. M. tangi sp. nov. Scale bars 0.30 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
-1A), that of sternite VIII slightly protruding backwards (
<figureCitation box="[741,813,1672,1697]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="11.[151,249,1799,1821]" captionTargetBox="[178,1407,419,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-122@11.[151,1436,409,1778]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 2. Forebody: A. Megalinus hailuogouensis sp. nov.; B. M. ningxiaensis sp. nov.; C. M. tangi sp. nov. Scale bars 0.30 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
-1B). Tergite IX symmetrical, connected mediobasally. Sternite IX asymmetrical, with gradually-sharpened base and broadly arcuate posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1225,1295,1708,1733]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="11.[151,249,1799,1821]" captionTargetBox="[178,1407,419,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-122@11.[151,1436,409,1778]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 2. Forebody: A. Megalinus hailuogouensis sp. nov.; B. M. ningxiaensis sp. nov.; C. M. tangi sp. nov. Scale bars 0.30 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
-1C). Tergite X symmetrical and narrow, with slightly rounded base and subtruncated posterior margin, 
<emphasis box="[1173,1243,1745,1768]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">in situ</emphasis>
broadly exposed between tergite IX (
<figureCitation box="[383,454,1780,1805]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="11.[151,249,1799,1821]" captionTargetBox="[178,1407,419,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-122@11.[151,1436,409,1778]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 2. Forebody: A. Megalinus hailuogouensis sp. nov.; B. M. ningxiaensis sp. nov.; C. M. tangi sp. nov. Scale bars 0.30 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
-1D). Median lobe of aedeagus elliptical, large sized (
<figureCitation box="[1078,1149,1780,1805]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="11.[151,249,1799,1821]" captionTargetBox="[178,1407,419,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-122@11.[151,1436,409,1778]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 2. Forebody: A. Megalinus hailuogouensis sp. nov.; B. M. ningxiaensis sp. nov.; C. M. tangi sp. nov. Scale bars 0.30 mm." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
-1E), basal piece without transparent, membranous medial-longitudinal band, anterior portion subcylindrical, 
<quantity box="[1097,1201,1816,1841]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.23">0.23 mm</quantity>
; basal bulb 
<quantity box="[1336,1436,1816,1841]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="0.82">0.82 mm</quantity>
long. Parameres symmetrical, elongate, slightly longer than 1/3 of basal bulb. Internal sac with two rows of spines, left one more transverse and larger; basal part crossed and with dense small spines.
</paragraph>
